.SH "Detailed Description"
.PP 
class: \fBPopen\fP This is the single most important class in the whole library and glues together all the helper classes to provide a common interface to the client\&.

.PP
API's provided by the class: \fBPopen\fP({"cmd"}, output{\&.\&.}, error{\&.\&.}, \&.\&.\&.\&.) Command provided as a sequence\&. \fBPopen\fP("cmd arg1", output{\&.\&.}, error{\&.\&.}, \&.\&.\&.\&.) Command provided in a single string\&. \fBwait()\fP - Wait for the child to exit\&. \fBretcode()\fP - The return code of the exited child\&. send(\&.\&.\&.) - Send input to the input channel of the child\&. communicate(\&.\&.\&.) - Get the output/error from the child and close the channels from the parent side\&. 
